        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 2:14PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 214 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southeast of Waynesville, or near Black Balsam Area, moving
northwest at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Graveyard Fields, Black Balsam Area, part of the Blue Ridge Parkway,
Sunburst, and Cruso.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
